properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued January 1 at 4:25AM AKST until January 1 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions occurring. Near zero visibility in
snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches. Southwest winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Northern Kachemak Bay including Homer and the Homer
Bluff.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM AKST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on poor road conditions. Areas of blowing snow
are producing white-out conditions. Travel will be hazardous
through the morning.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Conditions will be slow to improve through
the afternoon.
properties.instruction:
weather to stay safe. Dress for cold conditions.

A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM AKST THIS MORNING FOR NORTHERN KACHEMAK BAY
